## Additional Terms for POS SDK 7220

### Hardware Compatibility Notice
This software is specifically designed for and tested with the New 7220 POS device. 
While it may work with other POS devices, full compatibility and support are only 
guaranteed for the intended hardware platform.

### Security and Compliance Notice
This software includes security features designed to meet PCI-DSS compliance 
requirements. However, achieving and maintaining compliance is the responsibility 
of the end user and depends on proper implementation, configuration, and 
operational procedures.

### Commercial Use
This software is licensed under the MIT License, which allows for commercial use. 
However, users are responsible for ensuring compliance with all applicable laws, 
regulations, and industry standards in their jurisdiction.

### Support and Warranty
This software is provided without warranty or support. For commercial support, 
training, or consulting services, please contact the POS SDK 7220 team at 
support@pos-sdk-7220.com.

### Attribution
If you use this software in your project, we kindly request that you include 
attribution to the POS SDK 7220 project in your documentation, user interface, 
or other appropriate locations.

